<1ST_LINE>r p BC-INDIANAAt-A-Glance     05-03 0205</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-INDIANA At-A-Glance,200</2ND_LINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here, at a glance, are the methods for picking
delegates from Indiana to attend the 1988 Democratic and Republican
national conventions this summer.
</TEXT>
<HEAD>DEMOCRATS</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   Method: Primary
   Date: Tuesday, May 3
   Presidential filing deadline: Friday, March 4, 1988
   Pledged delegates: 79 Super delegates: 6 TOTAL: 85
   Delegates allocated: Tuesday, May 3
   Selection of delegates:Sunday, June 5 and Monday, June 6
   
   The results of the Indiana primary on May 3 will govern the
proportional allocation of all of the state's 79 pledged Democratic
National Convention delegates among the presidential candidates.
</TEXT>
<HEAD>REPUBLICANS</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   Method: Primary
   Date: Tuesday, May 3
   Presidential filing deadline: Friday, March 4, 1988
   Delegates: 51
   Delegates allocated: Tuesday, May 3 and Thursday, June 9
   Selection of delegates: Wednesday, June 8 and Thursday, June 9
   
   Indiana Republicans allocate their national convention delegates
at the primary election on May 3 and at the state convention on
June 9.
   Three delegates from each of the state's 10 congressional
districts will be awarded to presidential candidates on a
winner-take-all basis in each district.
   The remaining 21 national convention delegates will be chosen at
large by the state convention. Their allocation will not be
governed by results of the primary.
</TEXT>
