<DATELINE>PEORIA, Ill. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A woman accused of stabbing a man in the
head with a 12-inch-long bayonet after he dropped a beer can in her
yard has been charged with aggravated battery, authorities said.
   Oakre Johnson was charged in Peoria County Circuit Court on
Monday, said county Sheriff's Sgt. Daniel Basfield. Bond was set at
$15,000, and a preliminary hearing was scheduled May 27.
   The 51-year-old Peoria woman is accused of attacking Steven C.
Johnson, 37, in a parking lot Saturday after he refused to pick up
the empty beer can, Basfield said.
   When officers arrived, Ms. Johnson was sitting on her porch with
the bayonet, according to a police report.
   Johnson was treated for cuts on the back of his head, forehead
and chin.
   Basfield said he did not believe Johnson and Ms. Johnson were
related.
