<HEAD>Iranian Attack Shuts Down UAE Oilfield</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NICOSIA, Cyprus (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An Iranian attack on a United Arab
Emirates' offshore oil field in the Persian Gulf has shut it down
for at least two months, the Middle East Economic Survey said.
   The weekly newsletter said the Mubarak oil field had been
producing between 8,000 and 9,000 barrels of oil a day during
recent months.
   The Iranian naval attack on April 18 came after U.S. forces
destroyed two Iranian oil platforms in the gulf in retaliation for
Iran's alleged sowing of a mine that damaged a U.S. warship the
previous week.
   Gulf-based shipping executives were puzzled by the attack
because Iran receives half the net revenues from the oil field.
</TEXT>
