<HEAD>Dukakis Building Big Lead in California, Poll Shows</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN FRANCISCO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Michael Dukakis has tripled his lead over
Jesse Jackson among California Democrats since March and out polls
his presidential campaign opponent in every part of the state,
according to a new survey.
   The Massachusetts governor topped Jackson by 49-28 percent with
less than six weeks remaining until the June 7 California primary,
according to the San Francisco Examiner@NewsCenter 4 poll published
Monday.
   Another 19 percent were uncommitted, while Sen. Albert Gore of
Tennessee received 3 percent support and Sen. Paul Simon of
Illinois 1 percent.
   Sen. Albert Gore of Tennessee received 3 percent support and
Sen. Paul Simon of Illinois 1 percent.
   The poll of 702 registered Democrats, which was conducted by
Teichner Associates, carried a margin of error of plus or minus 3.8
percentage points.
   In a similar poll conducted by Teichner in March, Dukakis led
Jackson by 28-21 percent with 37 percent undecided and 14 percent
supporting other candidates.
