<HEAD>Tornadoes Funnel Through Kansas; Blizzard Belts Colorado</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   A severe storm droppped heavy snow on Colorado today after
whipping up several tornadoes in Kansas.
   More than a foot of snow fell on eastern Colorado, closing all
roads in and out of Limon.
   Strong winds brought blizzard conditions to eastern Colorado on
Monday night. Up to 12 inches fell in Strasburg and 6 inches in
Limon.
   In central Kansas, a tornado damaged a trailer at Cheney and
another briefly touched down in open country near Lyons on Monday
night. Several twisters were spotted around Lake Cheney and Lake
Afton.
   Showers and thunderstorms persisted over the area today. Showers
also prevailed from northern Louisiana and eastern Texas through
western Missouri, the Dakotas and the central High Plains.
   Cloudy skies and light rain continued in the Northeast, while
the Pacific Northwest received scattered showers.
   Fair skies extended from the Southeast to the Great Lakes region
and in the Southwest.
   Today's forecast called for rain from the northern Pacific Coast
across the Idaho Panhandle and northwest Montana; rain and
occasional thunderstorms from Arkansas across northeast Oklahoma,
Missouri, Kansas, Nebraska, southeastern South Dakota and western
Iowa.
   Temperatures were expected to reach the upper 40s over western
Nebraska; the 50s over New England, New York, the western half of
the Dakotas, the rest of western Nebraska, much of Colorado, and
the northern half of the Pacific coast; the 80s over Florida, the
central Gulf Coast states, Louisiana, southern Texas and southern
New Mexico; the 80s and 90s through the desert Southwest and
generally the 60s and 70s over the rest of the nation.
   Temperatures around the nation at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 18
degrees at Yellowstone National Park, Wyo., to 76 degrees at Key
West, Fla.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 58 fair; Boston 41 rain; Buffalo 39 fair;
Charleston, S.C. 53 fair; Cincinnati 54 fair; Cleveland 49 partly
cloudy; Detroit 47 fair; Miami 73 fair; New York 46 cloudy;
Philadelphia 45 fair; Pittsburgh 48 fair; Portland, Maine 41
cloudy; Washington 49 cloudy.
   _Central: Bismarck 40 rain; Chicago 53 fair; Dallas-Fort Worth
64 foggy; Denver 34 fair; Des Moines 62 partly cloudy; Indianapolis
52 fair; Kansas City 57 cloudy; Minneapolis-St. Paul 60 fair;
Nashville 55 fair; New Orleans 62 fair; St. Louis 63 fair.
   _West: Albuquerque 51 fair; Anchorage 45 cloudy; Las Vegas 56
fair; Los Angeles 57 fair; Phoenix 66 fair; Salt Lake City 38 fair;
San Diego 62 fair; San Francisco 52 cloudy; Seattle 42 fair.
   _Canada: Montreal 37 fair; Toronto 39 partly cloudy.
