<HEAD>Mudslide Hits Afghan Village, 35 Killed</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Najib is cq.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>MOSCOW (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A mudslide swept through a rural Afghan village,
killing 35 people and destroying hundreds of homes, Tass reported
today.
   Rescue and reconstruction workers had arrived in the village of
Rabotak in the Afghan province of Samangan, said the Soviet news
agency, which quoted the official Afghan news agency Bakhtar.
   The Moscow-aligned government of President Najib formed a
special commission to assess damage and provide relief, Tass said.
The agency gave no further details of the disaster, and did not say
when it occurred.
   Spring rains have caused many recent mudslides in mountainous
regions of Afghanistan and the Soviet republic of Kirgizia in
Central Asia.
