<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Popsicle Shooting, 1st Ld-Writethru, a0532,0169</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Teen Dies Defending Popsicle</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Adds one graf at end, police still searching for suspect</NOTE>
<DATELINE>BALTIMORE (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 16-year-old boy died after he was shot while
a friend fought with another teen-ager over a 15-cent cherry
Popsicle, police said.
   Clay Sands III, shot once in the abdomen Sunday on the street
near his home, died at University Hospital early Monday, said
Detective David H. Hollingsworth.
   A friend of Sands, 17-year-old Tracey Sheppard, said he asked
Sands to stay with him while Sheppard fought with a youth who he
claimed had grabbed a Popsicle out of his hand.
   While Sheppard and the youth fought, another youngster,
described as about 16, started fighting with Sands, pulled a
handgun and shot him, police said.
   ``We were pretty close. We always did things together. He was
like a big brother. I'm short for my age. He always looked out for
me,'' Sheppard said of Sands.
   Police were still looking for the suspect, Hollingsworth said.
</TEXT>
