<1ST_LINE>r a PM-Dial-a-Porn     05-03 0239</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Dial-a-Porn,0247</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Delaware State Workers Rack Up `976' Calls</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DOVER, Del. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A six-week audit shows dozens of calls were
made to a dial-a-porn service from a state-owned telephone in a
prison warden's home, according to a report published today.
   ``This is the first I've ever heard of it,'' Gander Hill Prison
Warden Howard R. Young told The (Wilmington) Morning News on Monday.
   ``I don't know who would do it, other than my oldest son or my
daughter. My daughter's the only one there at five. I'll be talking
to my daughter and whoever when I get home,'' Young said.
   The audit also turned up ``976'' calls from several state
offices. At the state Justice Department, ``Sports Phone'' seemed
to be the favorite, while calls at the Department of Transportation
were traced mostly to pornographic numbers.
   Between early November and late December, 93 calls were made
mostly during the day from various agency telephones.
   The number of calls showed ``surprisingly'' little abuse of
state telephone lines, Administrative Services Secretary George E.
Hale said Monday.
   The survey turned up $75.33 in direct tolls for calls to special
service lines, although the report did not detail costs charged for
calls on the state's wide-area, bulk-calling service.
   ``I reached the conclusion that, from a financial standpoint,
it's not a significant problem,'' Hale said. ``Although it does
raise questions about what the individual employees involved have
to do with their time.''
</TEXT>
