<2ND_LINE>AM-Netherlands-Boeing,0138</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Landing Gear Flap Forces Dutch Jumbo To Make Emergency Landing</HEAD>
<DATELINE>AMSTERDAM, Netherlands (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A KLM Boeing 747 airliner
developed landing gear problems on a flight from Los Angeles and
made a successful emergency landing Tuesday, an airline spokesman
said.
   None of the jumbo jet's 196 passengers and 16 crew was injured
after the 11-hour non-stop flight from California, KLM spokesman
Hugo Baas said.
   ``The right leg of the plane's main landing gear failed to lock
into position,'' Baas told The Associated Press.
   After the emergency services of Amsterdam's Schiphol Airport
went on full alert, the plane landed safely at 11:05 a.m., said
Baas. He said damage to the jumbo jet was minor.
   For safety reasons, passengers and crew left the plane while it
was still on the runway, Baas said.
</TEXT>
