<HEAD>Jackson Reports Nearly $210,000 in 1987 Income</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Jesse Jackson and his wife Jacqueline reported
income of nearly $210,000 during 1987 and paid one-fourth of that
in federal income taxes, according to copies of their tax returns
released today.
   Jackson's Democratic presidential campaign released copies of
his returns for 1984 through 1987.
   The bulk of the Jacksons' income last year, $159,000, came from
Personalities International Inc., a corporation headed by Mrs.
Jackson that provides management for personalities, and which
handles Jackson's earnings from speeches and publications.
   They reported Jackson received $46,535 for unspecified business
services. Together with dividends, interest and other income, their
1987 unadjusted gross income was $209,358. They paid $53,631 in
federal taxes.
   The Jacksons' total income was up from $59,453 in 1984, the year
of his first presidential campaign.
