<HEAD>Moslem Bandits Kill Vice Mayor, Five Workers</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ZAMBOANGA, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Moslem guerrillas killed a town
official and five Philippine employees of an American-run company
in two separate incidents, officials said Tuesday.
   Rebels on Monday shot and killed Vice Mayor Hadji Jallao of
Patikul on Sulu Island, about 600 miles south of Manila, according
to the military's Southern Command.
   The assailants made off with the official's bag, which contained
about $700, the command said. His 14-year-old companion was wounded.
   On nearby Basilan Island, Moslem rebels ambushed a truck of the
American-run Sime-Darby Rubber Co. last Thursday and killed five
farmworkers, the mayor of the town of Lamitan said.
   Mayor Wilfredo Furigay said the workers were returning from the
fields when they were attacked. He said the rebels were extorting
money from plantation owners and transport operators.
   Moslem rebels are fighting for a separate state in the southern
Philippines.
