<TEXT>
   Secretary of State George P. Shultz met
Tuesday with the president of Chile's opposition Christian
Democratic Party, Patricio Aylwin, and reaffirmed U.S. support for
a transition to democratic rule in Chile.
   The meeting occurred as Chileans are preparing for a yes-or-no
vote later this year on a single presidential candidate, who is
expected to be President Augusto Pinochet.
   Aylwin expressed confidence that opposition leaders have the
votes to defeat the expected Pinochet candidacy, which would force
a subsequent open election for president.
   He said opposition parties have formed a united front against
Pinochet.
