<HEAD>Reagan Asks Congress To Extend Fishing Accord With East Germany</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Reagan asked Congress on Tuesday to
grant a two-year extension of a fishery agreement between the
United States and East Germany.
   The agreement was first signed in 1983 and has been renewed
periodically.
