<1ST_LINE>r a AM-MethodistBishops     05-03 0097</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Methodist Bishops,0098</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Openings Set For Four New Methodist Bishops</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Methodist Meeting, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ST. LOUIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The United Methodist governing conference has
approved splitting of four episcopal areas, mostly in the South,
which would mean an addition of four bishops to the nation's
second-largest Protestant body.
   The measure allows the three jurisdictions in which the
episcopal areas lie to divide the areas if they choose, although
determinations still must be made about funding and
constitutionality of the change.
   The episcopal areas that could be affected are Dallas-Fort
Worth, Texas; Birmingham, Ala; Atlanta; and Indiana.
</TEXT>
