   The tanks rolled north of Israel's self-designated security zone
and backed up hundreds of heavily armed troops who combed Lebanon's
rugged southern foothills, searching for Palestinian guerrillas.
   Lebanese police said Syrian forces went on ``maximum alert'' as
Israeli fighters neared Syrian troops. No clashes were reported.
