<2ND_LINE>BC-Park-Kentucky,0156</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Park Buys Newspaper in Somerset, Ky.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Park Communications Inc. said Tuesday that it
has acquired the Commonwealth-Journal, a daily newspaper in
Somerset, Ky.
   Park, a diversified media company based in Ithaca, N.Y., said it
purchased the five-day daily and Sunday paper, its companion
paid-weekly newspaper, McCreary County Record, and two
controlled-distribution weeklies: Shopper Stopper and Lake
Cumberland Advisor.
   The purchase price wasn't disclosed.
   Together, the four publications serve more than 32,000 homes in
six southcentral Kentucky counties.
   George A. Joplin III, president of Commonwealth-Journal Co.,
said the newspaper had been operated by his family for 60 years but
that his health required that he withdraw from the operation.
   The Commonwealth-Journal is Park's first daily newspaper in
Kentucky.
   Park owns and operates 39 daily newspapers, 82 other
publications, seven television stations and 19 radio stations in 23
states.
</TEXT>
