<HEAD>London Shares End Mixed</HEAD>
<NOTE>EDS: RECASTS throughout to UPDATE with late trading activity,
closing index; No pickup</NOTE>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Share prices ended mixed Tuesday on the London
Stock Exchange, with gains in most international stocks the only
feature in an otherwise torpid market.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index finished at
1,807.2, up 5 points, or 0.3 percent, from Friday's close.
   British financial markets were closed Monday for a bank holiday.
   Volume was a light 335 million shares, down from 417.5 million
shares on Friday.
   Although Wall Street opened slightly higher Tuesday, dealers
said the New York market wasn't providing needed direction for
London traders.
   The greatest gains in London were in the dollar-earning stocks,
which rose on expectations that the U.S. dollar might bounce back,
capping the British pound's recent rise, dealers said.
   The outlook for a higher dollar was based on market belief that
short-term U.S. interest rates might rise, they said.
</TEXT>
