<1ST_LINE>r f BC-BusinessHighlights 1stAdd   05-03 0475</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Business Highlights, 1st Add,0498</2ND_LINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The New York Stock Exchange is requiring members
to submit daily reports of their program trades, a move designed to
help the exchange analyze market volatility.
   Under the new rule, NYSE members and member firms must submit a
log of program trades made for customers or for their own accounts,
including trades executed in other markets, by the close of the
second business day following the trades, the exchange said in a
statement Tuesday.
   Members are not required, however, to identify customers for
whom program trades were executed.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Trading was halted for more than 2{ hours on the
Chicago Mercantile Exchange after water from a burst pipe flooded
the exchange's telecommunications room, disabling its automated
price quotation system.
   The Chicago Mercantile Exchange is the leading U.S. market for
stock-index and livestock futures, and the trading shutdown on
Tuesday had a quieting effect on the nation's other financial
markets, analysts said.
   Exchange officials called the trading halt at 8:05 a.m. local
time, 45 minutes after the opening of trading in foreign currency
and Treasury bill futures.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>HOUSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Southdown Inc. and Moore McCormack Resources Inc.
say they will sell a Moore McCormack energy subsidiary for about
$148.7 million to CanadianOxy Offshore Production Co.
   The two resource companies said the proceeds from the sale of
Moore McCormack Energy Inc. will be used to help pay off loans made
to Southdown for its recent $512 million acquisition of Moore
McCormack Resources.
   CanadianOxy Offshore Production is a subsidiary of Occidental
Petroleum Corp., a major oil company based in Los Angeles.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Xerox Corp. has marked the 50th anniversary of
plain-paper copying with a new line of products that includes its
first personal copier, made for Xerox by Japanese rival Sharp Corp.
   The machines in the new 50 Series introduced Tuesday have more
features and higher price tags than members of Xerox's successful
10 Series, which helped the company begin to regain market share
from Japanese competitors.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>ST. PAUL, Minn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Future airline competition will revolve
more around service than price, the chief executive of United
Airlines says.
   Stephen Wolf, who also has headed Continental Airlines, Tiger
International Inc. and the former Republic Airlines, told a group
of business editors and writers Tuesday that ``service will be the
prime determinant of how well any airline competes in the future.''
</TEXT>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   The stock market gained ground Tuesday, as the Dow Jones average
of 30 industrials rose 15.09 to 2,058.36.
   Bond prices rose modestly in light trading.
   The dollar rose narrowly on domestic markets but fell overseas
in foreign exchange trading.
   Gold futures prices dipped to their lowest levels in more than
six weeks, but energy futures rallied, cattle futures rose and
grains and soybeans fell.
</TEXT>
